fields.description: Sounds created as part of my PhD thesis to demonstrate different types of sound transformations using spectral techniques. All done in 1989.
fields.name: morphs

fields.description: Morphing between a cello note and the word cello done computing the short-time Fourier transform of two recorded sounds, interpolating their spectral data and performing the inverse transform. Done in the early 1990's on a NeXT computer.

Morphing between the sound of a boat creaking and a voice saying "We were away a while ago", done computing the short-time Fourier transform of two recorded sounds, interpolating their spectral data and performing the inverse transform. Done in the early 1990's on a NeXT computer.

Morphing between a cat's meow and a voice saying "We were away a while ago", done computing the short-time Fourier transform of two recorded sounds, interpolating their spectral data and performing the inverse transform. Done in the early 1990's on a NeXT computer.

Morphing between the sound of a gong and a voice
saying "We were away a while ago", done computing the short-time Fourier transform of two recorded sounds, interpolating their spectral data and performing the inverse transform. Done in the early 1990's on a NeXT computer.

Morphing between the sound of a plane and a voice
saying "We were away a while ago", done computing the short-time Fourier transform of two recorded sounds, interpolating their spectral data and performing the inverse transform. Done in the early 1990's on a NeXT computer.
logarithmic sinusoid sweep with some amplitude variation.
Dirty electric fuzzy sound. Changed with a dynamic delay.
Glitchy busy ghost. Sparkly and Stereo.
Conversation amongst friends, laughter, squeeky chair. Recorded with an el'cheapo condeser stereo mike onto MD. Stereo, but with a telephone type of vibe too it ;-)
